# My Chat App Workflow

## Core Expectations

- Implement changes end-to-end, do not stop at analysis.
- Never commit or push unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Do not amend commits unless explicitly requested.
- Do not edit secrets or env files unless explicitly requested.
- Keep changes minimal and avoid touching unrelated files.
- Never revert unrelated user changes.

## Access and Permissions Safety

- Any change in reports or accounting access logic must preserve:
  - author can edit own report;
  - superuser can edit any report;
  - non-owner non-superuser cannot edit чужой report.
- If access behavior changes, add or update a smoke test scenario.

## Mandatory Verification

- Run the fastest relevant checks before final response:
  - Dart/Flutter: `flutter analyze` on changed files.
  - Node backend: `node --check` on changed files.
  - Accounting/reports backend: relevant smoke scripts.
- Prefer targeted checks first; run broad suites only when needed.
- Do not claim verification unless command/manual validation was actually performed.

## Context Efficiency

Use less context **without skipping required work**:

- Prefer **narrow tools first** (grep, one file read, semantic search with a bounded path) instead of exploratory reads across the whole repo when the user named a module or area.
- For **large files**, read chunks (start/middle/end or search hits) until the edit site is clear; avoid returning huge raw dumps in replies—cite `start:end:path` instead.
- **Do not omit** mandated verification (analyze, `--check`, smokes where required), accounting/report access rules, or end-to-end implementation to “save tokens.”
- **Avoid redundant duplication**: don’t paste the same long snippet twice or re-quote unchanged code blocks; summarize deltas.
- Prefer **skills** (`my-chat-app-architecture`) and **scoped rules** (globs) over re-deriving layout from scratch when the answer is documented there.

## Response Style

- Report what was changed, what was verified, and any remaining risk.
- If a scenario cannot be fully validated due to environment data, state it explicitly.
